history.content: You don't need Physics 7b at all.  There's no E/M knowledge required.  And Javey covers everything you need to know (aka he doesn't assume any prior knowledge). As for "mathy" EE classes, my first thought is the 120 series (though 120 is a prerequisite for the other classes besides 122,127,126). You could take EE 226B.

How feasible is it to take EE 143 without Physics 7B? I have taken 16A/B. 

On another note, I am looking for a mathy EE class that I can still add. 127 is full, I took 126, and I am currently taking 120.. Is there any other math heavy EE classes?
history.subject: EE 143 without Physics 7B?
